    <h1>Guide to Breathing techniques.</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>An average human eats 89,790 meals in <strong>lifetime</strong>,=
 spends 229,961 hours of his <strong>life</strong> sleeping, and takes <str=
ong>8,409,600 breaths in a Year</strong>!!</p>
<p>Breathing, the very sign of life, a simple and automatic act and yet is =
the most neglected aspect of daily routine. We put a lot of efforts and foc=
us on Eating right, and sleeping adequately, which is not sufficient for op=
timum health and physical state if we don=E2=80=99t know how to breathe rig=
ht.</p>
<p>Breathing has a deep impact on mental and physical state and intentional=
ly practicing breathing the right way has the ability to enhance mental foc=
us, physical performance, relieve stress and aid recovery after workout.</p=
>
<p>This document aims to detail the different breathing techniques which ca=
n influence the autonomic balance. Different breathing patterns discussed b=
elow have a different effect and can be used as a means of mind-body connec=
tion. Practice these breathing techniques regularly for better results and =
benefits.</p>
